	"description": "A portfolio is a great way to show off your skills to potential employers. And\nit&#x27;s especially helpful for entry-level developers who might not have any\nprofessional work experience.\n\nHowever, a common problem you might have when building a portfolio is knowing\nwhat to include in it.\n\nIs the simple web page you built for a course good enough to put on your\nwebsite? Do you have to only include projects you were paid for, or can you\ninclude even the smallest of things? Is there a &#x27;right&#x27; number of",
